               <head>Ten miscellaneous texts</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>A collection of treatises on philosophy, Sufism, medicine, astronomy, grammar, etc.</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008109242 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh87000152" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16270-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="65v"> f. 1v-65r.</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="en" key="work_22121">Commentary on a metaphysical treatise</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Commentary on a metaphysical treatise, both in Arabic.
This is probably <title>Shawāriq al-ilhām</title>, a commentary on <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_12392936" ref="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n82136884" role="ant">Naṣīr al-Dīn Ṭūsī</persName>’s <title>Tajrīd al-i‘tiqād</title>. By <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_16145304708378611094" ref="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n86830767" role="aut">‘Abd al-Razzāq ‘Alī al-Lāhījī</persName> (d. 1072/1661), a student of Mullā Ṣadrā. See EI2 V, pp. 604-5. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Undated.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <filiation />
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_16145304708378611094">‘Abd al-Razzāq ‘Alī al-Lāhījī</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085" n="2" xml:id="Uk_Or_16270-item2">
                     <locus from="66r" to="97v">ff. 66r-97v</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22122">Radd al-‘ayb ‘an Lisān al-Ghayb</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22122">رد العیب عن لسان الغیب</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A defence of the theological soundness of verses by the Sufi poet<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_56731778" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n79086812" role="aut">Ḥāfiẓ</persName>. By Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad ibn Salīm al-Shīrāzī. Completed 1219/1804-5.
                        </p>
                        <p>This work is extremely rare: only one other copy is recorded in reference sources. </p>
                        <p>Manuscript dated 1228/1813.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7365">Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad ibn Salīm al-Shīrāzī.</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7365">محمد بن محمد بن سلیم الشیرازی</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85082139" n="3" xml:id="Uk_Or_16270-item3">
                     <locus from="98v" to="137v">ff  98v-137v</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_4318"> Risālah dar ‘ilm-i ḥisāb</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_4318">رساله در علم حساب</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A treatise on arithmetic, comprising 3 maqālahs.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100849" n="4" xml:id="Uk_Or_16270-item4">
                     <locus from="138v" to="152v">ff. 138v-152v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Part of a treatise on philosophy and aesthetics. </p>
                        <p>Copied in 1231/1815-16.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85072735" n="5" xml:id="Uk_Or_16270-item5">
                     <locus from="152v" to="154v">ff. 152v-154v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Part (or whole) of a tract on epistemology. </p>
                        <p>Copied in 1231/1815-16.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85025414" n="6" xml:id="Uk_Or_16270-item6">
                     <locus from="155v" to="168v">ff. 155v-168v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Mukhtaṣar dar ma‘rifat-i taqvīm,
the well-known treatise on astronomy and chronology, in 3 faṣls, by Naṣīr al-Dīn Ṭūsī. </p>
                        <p>Undated; early 13th/19th century.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_12392936">Ṭūsī, Naṣīr al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad, 1201-1274</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_12392936">طوسي، نصير الدين محمد بن مجمد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_5032">Mukhtaṣar dar maʼrifat-i taqvīm</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_5032">
مختصر در معرفت تقویم</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian. </textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85072983 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85072984" n="7" xml:id="Uk_Or_16270-item7">
                     <locus from="169v" to="195v">ff. 169v-195v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>On recitation of the Qur’ān, partly in verse. </p>
                        <p>Copied in 1233/1817-18.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22123">Kitāb-i tajvīd</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22123">کتاب التجوید</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh86000279" n="8" xml:id="Uk_Or_16270-item8">
                     <locus from="196r" to="201r">ff. 196r-201r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Undated: 13th/19th century.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="en" key="work_22124">Extract from a grammatical work in Arabic. </title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89004629" n="9" xml:id="Uk_Or_16270-item9">
                     <locus from="202v" to="213r">ff. 202v-213r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>

Tract on number tables and figures and their occult properties (khavāṣṣ).
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22125">Risālah dar vifq-i a‘dād</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22125">رساله در وقف اعداد</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh93009493" n="10" xml:id="Uk_Or_16270-item10">
                     <locus from="214v" to="240r">ff.  214v-240r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collection of texts: this mainly comprises, on f. 214v-234r, <title>Anvār-i ḥikmat</title>, on ethics and Sufism, by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_59391721" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/nr92027650" role="aut">Yūsufī</persName> (FNKhF II/1, pp. 1545-6); also three poems concerned with medical matters and one concerning miserliness.

                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22126">Majmū‘ah dar ṭibb va ghayr-i ān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22126">مجموعه در طب و غیر آن</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_59391721">Harawī, Muḥammad ibn Yūsuf, active 16th century</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_59391721">هروي، محمد بن يوسف</persName>
                     </author>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
